var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"#SingularModes.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"Software package written in Julia for the propagation of transverse laser modes through turbulent media with particular focus on singular modes. By construction, singular modes are the optimal communication modes which are obtained via a singular value decomposition of a given channel's transmission matrix.","title":"SingularModes.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Project-status","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"This package emerged from a PhD project and is based on the following publications:\n\nBachmann, D., Isoard, M., Shatokhin, V. N., Sorelli, G., Treps, N., and Buchleitner, A. (2023). Highly Transmitting Modes of Light in Dynamic Atmospheric Turbulence. Physical Review Letters, 130(7):073801. 10.1103/physrevlett.130.073801.\n\nBachmann, D., Klug, A., Isoard, M., Shatokhin, V. N., Sorelli, G., Buchleitner, A., and Forbes, A. (2024). Universal Crosstalk of Twisted Light in Random Media. Physical Review Letters, 132(6):063801. 10.1103/physrevlett.132.063801.\n\nBachmann, D., Isoard, M., Shatokhin, V. N., Sorelli, G., and Buchleitner, A. (2025). Accurate Zernike-corrected phase screens for arbitrary power spectra. Optical Engineering, 64(5):058102. 10.1117/1.OE.64.5.058102.","title":"Project status"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Prerequisites:-Install-Julia","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"You need a running copy of Julia to use this package. We recommend to install it via the package manager of your system, e.g., pacman or apt-get on Arch or Debian-based Linux, respectively.\n\n# Arch linux\nsudo pacman -S julia\n\n# Debian-based Linux\nsudo apt-get install julia\n\nOn macOS, Julia can be installed via the package manager Homebrew which is recommended for easy updates later on. Install Homebrew and Julia:\n\n# macOS\n# Install Homebrew\n/bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"\n# Install Julia\nbrew install julia","title":"Prerequisites: Install Julia"},{"category":"section","location":"#Install-the-SingularModes.jl-package","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"Once Julia is running on your system, the SingularModes package can straightforwardly be installed via Julia's internal package manager.\n\njulia> ]\npkg> add SingularModes","title":"Install the SingularModes.jl package"},{"category":"section","location":"#Package-structure","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"This software package is structured as follows:\n\n.\n│\n├── src                    [Julia modules]\n│   ├── BasicFunctions.jl  [library of general functions and definitions]\n│   ├── FigureDefaults.jl  [default settings for plotting]\n│   ├── ModeGeneration.jl  [library for transverse mode generation]\n│   ├── Phasescreens.jl    [library for phase screen generation]\n│   ├── Plotting.jl        [library for plotting routines]\n│   ├── PowerSpectra.jl    [library of power spectra for different media]\n│   ├── Propagation.jl     [library for all functions related to propagation]\n│   └── Statistics.jl      [library for the statistical analysis of phase screens]\n│\n├── docs                   [documentation of the package]\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── examples               [code examples]\n│   ├── static             [cached arrays of LG/ZK/KL modes for faster computation]\n│   │\n│   ├── parameters.jl      [sample parameter file]\n│   ├── LG-Beams.jl        [sample code for the propagtion of Lagurre-Gaussian beams]\n│   ├── Singularmodes.jl   [sample code for the computation of singular modes]\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── tests                  [code tests]\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── LICENSE                [GPL-3.0-or-later]\n├── README.md              [Short documentation]\n│\n└── ...\n\nThe constituent Julia modules are documented below.\n\n","title":"Package structure"},{"category":"section","location":"#BasicFunctions.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"BasicFunctions.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#FigureDefaults.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"FigureDefaults.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#ModeGeneration.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"ModeGeneration.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#PhaseScreens.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"PhaseScreens.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Plotting.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"Plotting.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#PowerSpectra.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"PowerSpectra.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Propagation.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"Propagation.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Statistics.jl","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"","title":"Statistics.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Examples","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"TBC...","title":"Examples"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.cart2pol-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"cart2pol(x, y)\n\nConvert Cartesian coordinates to polar coordinates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.cart2pol"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.ft-Tuple{Array, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ft(g, delta=1)\n\nMulti dimensional Fourier transfrom with optional gridspacing d = 1`.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.ft"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.ift-Tuple{Array, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ift(g, delta_f=1)\n\nInverse multi dimensional Fourier transfrom. See also ft.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.ift"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.inner_circ-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"inner_circ(a; nans=false)\n\nSet all elements outside of an inscribed circle to zero or NaN (nans=true).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.inner_circ"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.meshgrid-Tuple{Vector, Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"meshgrid(x, y)\n\nRectangular meshgrid array from the vectors x and y.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.meshgrid"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.msum-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"msum(mode)\n\nTotal power of a mode.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.msum"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.norm_coeff-Tuple{Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"norm_coeff(vec)\n\nNormalizes the vector vec s.t. sum(abs.2(vec))=1.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.norm_coeff"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.norm_mode-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"norm_mode(mode)\n\nNormalize the intensity of a mode such that the total power yields one.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.norm_mode"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.pol2cart-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pol2cart(th, r)\n\nConvert polar to Cartesian coordinates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.pol2cart"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.print_paras-Tuple{Real, Number, Integer, Integer, Real, Real, Real, Real, Real, Real, Real, Real, Integer, Integer, Real, Real, Real, String, Real, Real, Real, Integer, Integer, Real, Integer, Real, Real, Real, Real, Real, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"print_paras(datdir,\n    Rphys, outin, zzR,\n    N, Nin,\n    Rin, RoutC, Rout, din, dout, wvl, z,\n    w0, nmax, jlmax, zR, nhigh, ratio,\n    spec, r0, l0, L0, sh, jzmax,\n    rs, ns, sr2,\n    vmean, vstd, tv, deltat, Ts)\n\nPrint parameters from parameters.jl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.print_paras"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.rayleigh_waist-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"rayleigh_waist(z, wvl)\n\nDetermine beam waist such that z = zR (Rayleigh length). This leads to the smallest possible output aperture.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.rayleigh_waist"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.rect-Tuple{Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"rect(x; w=1, nans=false)\n\nRectangle function returns one if x is within (-w/2, w/2) else zero or NaN (nans=true).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.rect"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.struct_fcn2_ft-Tuple{Matrix, Matrix, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"struct_fcn2_ft(ph, mask, delta)\n\nStructure function based on FT from [Schmidt (2010)]. Very sensitive to boundaries, needs zeropadding. Not tested. Recommended not to use.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.struct_fcn2_ft"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.wopt-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"wopt(D, Df)\n\nTheoretical beam width for optimal vacuum propagation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.wopt"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.BasicFunctions.zeropad-Tuple{Matrix, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zeropad(a, s)\n\nZeropad a matrix to the desired side length s.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.BasicFunctions.zeropad"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.FigureDefaults.set_fig_defaults-Tuple{}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"set_fig_defaults()\n\nSet defaults for plotting figures with the Plots package.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.FigureDefaults.set_fig_defaults"},{"category":"function","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration._default_N","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"_default_N(N, fpointsname)\n\nDefault gridsize N for LG and ZK modes. See also lg, zk, points2grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration._default_N"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.bcl-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"bcl(uin)\n\nFourier-based beam correlation length of an input beam profile uin`.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.bcl"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.besselbeam-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"besselbeam(x, y; z=0, wvl=1550e-9, beta=0, l=0, paraxial=true)\n\nPointwise Bessel mode function. For non-paraxial wave equation set paraxial=false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.besselbeam"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.besselgaussian-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"besselgaussian(x, y; w0=1, z=0, wvl=1550e-9, beta=0, l=0)\n\nPointwise Bessel-Gaussian mode function. See also besselbeam.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.besselgaussian"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.bg_mode-Tuple{}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"bg_mode(; N=256, R=1, kwargs...)\n\nShorthand for a single BG mode on a grid. See also besselgaussian, points2grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.bg_mode"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"hg(x, y; w0x=1, w0y=1, w0=1, z=0, wvl=1550e-9, m=0, n=0, d=1)\n\nPointwise Hermite-Gaussian mode function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg_1d-Tuple{Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"hg_1d(x, y; w0=1, z=0, wvl=1550e-9, m=0, d=1)\n\nPointwise one-dimensional Hermite-Gaussian mode function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg_1d"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg_mode-Tuple{}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"hg_mode(; N=256, R=1, kwargs...)\n\nShorthand for a single HG mode on a grid. See also hg, points2grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.hg_mode"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2mn-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"j2mn(j) = j2mn(j, hg=true)\n\nShorthand for reconversion of HG Noll indices. See also j2pl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2mn"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2nm-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"j2nm(j) = j2pl(j, zk=true)\n\nShorthand for reconversion of ZK Noll indices. See also j2pl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2nm"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2nmax-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"j2nmax(j)\n\nMaximal radial order nmax for a given superindex j. See also j2pl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2nmax"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2pl-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"j2pl(j, zk=false)\n\nReconversion of Noll superindex j to individual indices p, l for LG modes and n, m for ZK modes (with zk=true).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.j2pl"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.laguerre-Tuple{Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"laguerre(n, alpha, x)\n\nAssociated/generalized Laguerre polynomial with radial order n and azimuthal index alpha. Definition from wikipedia.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.laguerre"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.lg-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"lg(x, y; w0=1, z=0, wvl=1550e-9, p=0, l=0, d=1, j=0)\n\nPointwise Lagurre-Gaussian mode function. See also laguerre.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.lg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.lg_mode-Tuple{}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"lg_mode(; N=256, R=1, kwargs...)\n\nShorthand for a single LG mode on a grid. See also lg, points2grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.lg_mode"},{"category":"function","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.make_grid","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"make_grid(N, R)\n\nMeshgrid of size N x N with sidelength 2R.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.make_grid"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mn2j-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"mn2j(m, n) = pl2j(m, n, hg=true)\n\nShorthand for HG Noll indices. See also pl2j.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mn2j"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mode_pyramid-Tuple{Function, Integer, Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"mode_pyramid(fpoints, nmax, N, R; jmax=0, threads=true, kwargs...)\n\nGenerate a pyramid array of a given mode via fpoints, i.e., kwargs... -> fpoints. See also lg, zk. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mode_pyramid"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mode_pyramid_load-Tuple{Function, Integer, Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"mode_pyramid_load(fpoints, nmax, N, R; kwargs...)\n\nLoad the mode pyramid from file (currently disabled). See also mode_pyramid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.mode_pyramid_load"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.nm2j-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"nm2j(n, m) = pl2j(n, m, zk=true)\n\nShorthand for ZK Noll indices. See also pl2j.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.nm2j"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.nmax2j-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"nmax2j(j)\n\nMaximal superindex j for a given radial order nmax. See also j2pl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.nmax2j"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.noll_pyramid-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"noll_pyramid(nmax)\n\nPrint a pyramid of Noll indices up to the radial order nmax. See also j2pl, pl2j.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.noll_pyramid"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl(l; w0=1)\n\nPhase correlation length based on Eq.~(11) in [Leonhard (2015)].\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_arc-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl_arc(l; w0=1)\n\nPhase correlation arc.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_arc"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_bg-Tuple{Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl_bg(l, beta; w0=1, mod=false)\n\nPhase correlation length for Bessel-Gaussian beams, as used in [Bachmann (2024)].\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_bg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_geo-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl_geo(l; w0=1)\n\nGeometric phase correlation length.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_geo"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_lim-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl_lim(l; w0=1)\n\nLarge l limit of the phase correlation length.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_lim"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_mod-Tuple{Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pcl_mod(l; w0=1)\n\nModified phase correlation length based on an isosceles triangle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pcl_mod"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pl2j-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pl2j(p, l; zk=false)\n\nDouble to single index conversion on basis of Noll's convention. Use p, l for LG modes, or n, m for ZK modes (with zk=true) or m, n for HG modes (with hg=true).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.pl2j"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.points2grid-Tuple{Function}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"points2grid(fpoints; N=1024, R=1, kwargs...)\n\nEvaluate the function fpoints on an N x N grid of sidelength 2R (default N=1024). Keywords arguments kwargs... are passed to fpoints. See also _default_N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.points2grid"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.r_z-Tuple{Number, Integer, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"r_z(r, n, m)\n\nRadial function of the Zernike polynomials based on [Noll (1976)], Eq. (1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.r_z"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.rho_mean_bg-Tuple{Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"rhomeanbg(l, beta; w0=1)\n\nMean radius of a Bessel-Gaussian beam.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.rho_mean_bg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zk-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk(x, y; R=1, j=1, angle=0)\n\nZernike polynomial with Noll index j, radius R and rotation angle angle. See also r_z.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zk"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zk_mode-Tuple{}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk_mode(; N=1024, R=1, kwargs...)\n\nShorthand for a single ZK mode on a grid. See also zk, points2grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zk_mode"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zka_load-Tuple{Integer, Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zka_load(nmax, darray; N=1024)\n\nGenerate an array of ZK pyramids for the multi-step propagation. Load from file if it exsists.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.ModeGeneration.zka_load"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.fourier_shift-Tuple{Matrix, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"fourier_shift(\n    a, dshift;\n    d=1\n    )\n\nSubpixel Fourier shift of a two-dimensional array a by distance dshift. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.fourier_shift"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.get_phzT-Tuple{Array, Vector, Vector, Real, Real}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"get_phzT(\n    phzB, Rarray, Tarray, vmean, vstd;\n    Norg=1024, rsw=0, kwargs...\n    )\n\nReturns a time array of z-arrays of wind-shifted phase screens based on a large underlaying screen z-array phzB with mean transverse wind velocity vmean and its standard deivation vstd at time time. The random seed for the wind velocity distribution defaults to rsw=0, and the subscreen side length to Norg=1024 pixels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.get_phzT"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.pFq_reg-Tuple{Vector, Vector, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"pFq(alist, blist, z)\n\nRegularized hypergeometric function. Relies on HypergeometricFunctions.jl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.pFq_reg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_ft-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_ft(\n    pow_spec, N, R, rs;\n    silent=false, kwargs...\n    )\n\nFourier phase screen for a given pow_spec on an N x N array with physical radius R and radom seed rs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_ft"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_hd-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_hd(\n    pow_spec, N, R, rs;\n    nmax=9, jzmax=0, zks=zks, phft=phft, nans=false, kwargs...\n    )\n\nHybrid phase screen for a given pow_spec on an N x N array with physical radius R and radom seed rs. Defaults to nmax=9 pyramidal levels for the constituent Zernike screen.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_hd"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_kl-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_kl(\n    pow_spec, N, R, rs;\n    nmax=9, jzmax=0, zks=zks, kls=kls, phft=phft, klsReturn=false,\n    kwargs...\n    )\n\nHybrid Karhunen-Loève phase screen for a given pow_spec on an N x N array with physical radius R and radom seed rs. Defaults to nmax=9 pyramidal levels for the constituent Zernike screen.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_kl"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_sh-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_sh(\n    pow_spec, N, R, rs;\n    sh=5, kwargs...\n    )\n\nSubharmonic Fourier phase screen for a given pow_spec on an N x N array with physical radius R and radom seed rs. Defaults to sh=5 subharmonic levels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_sh"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_x-Tuple{Function}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_x(\n    pow_spec;\n    N=1024, R=1, rs=0, kind=\"hd\", kwargs...\n    )\n\nWrapper function for single phase screens. Supported kinds are \"ft\", \"sh\", \"zk\", \"hd\", and \"kl\", see keyword arguments of the corresponding functions. Defaults to a hybrid phase screen with N=1024, R=1, and rs=0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_x"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_zk-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_zk(\n    pow_spec, N, R, rs;\n    nmax=9, jzmax=0, zks=zks, ascorr=ascorr, silent=false, kwargs...\n    )\n\nZernike phase screen for a given pow_spec on an N x N array with physical radius R and radom seed rs. Defaults to nmax=9 pyramidal levels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_zk"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.phz_x-Tuple{Function, Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ph_x(\n    pow_spec, Rarray;\n    N=1024, R=1, rs=0, kind=\"hd\", r0tot=0, kwargs...\n    )\n\nWrapper function for phase screen arrays along the z-axis specied via Rarray. Supported kinds are \"ft\", \"sh\", \"zk\", \"hd\", and \"kl\", see keyword arguments of the corresponding functions. Defaults to a hybrid phase screens with N=1024, R=1, and rs=0. The total Fried parameter has either to be specified via r0tot or multiplied manually for non-Kolmogorov turbulence.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.phz_x"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.screen_factor-NTuple{4, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"screen_factor(\n    vmean, vstd, tmax, R;\n    offset=0.1\n    )\n\nComputes the required size of a large, time-shifted phase screen based on the mean transverse wind velocity vmean, its standard deivation vstd, the maximally considered time tmax, and the smaller subscreen's radius R.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.screen_factor"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.wind_shift-Tuple{Array, Integer, Vector, Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"wind_shift(\n    phzB, Norg, Rarray, vmean, vstd, time;\n    rsw=0, offset=0.1, threads=true, kwargs...\n    )\n\nReturns a z-array of wind-shifted phase screens with resolution Norg x Norg based on a large underlaying screen array phzB with mean transverse wind velocity vmean and its standard deivation vstd at time time. The random seed for the wind velocity distribution defaults to rsw=0, the offset=0.1 defaults to a 10% margin from the large screens boundaries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.wind_shift"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_cov_atm-Tuple{Integer, Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk_cov_atm(j, jp, R; L0=Inf, alpha=5/3)\n\nAnalytical Zernike covariances for the atmospheric phase power spectra.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_cov_atm"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_cov_num-Tuple{Function, Integer, Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk_cov_num(power_spec, j, jp, R; kwargs...)\n\nNumerical Zernike covariances for arbitrary power_spec. All kwargs... are passed to power_spec.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_cov_num"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_covmat-Tuple{Function, Integer, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk_covmat(\n    pow_spec, nmax, R;\n    analytics=true, jmax=0, l0=0, alpha=5/3, kwargs...\n    )\n\nZernike covariance matrix obtained analytically for Kolmogorov and von Karman turbulence , else (or if analytics=false) numerically.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_covmat"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_overlap-Tuple{Matrix, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zk_overlap(\n    ph, zks\n    )\n\nComputes the overlap of a phase screen ph with the Zernike polynomials zks.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_overlap"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.clean_mode_plot-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"clean_mode_plot(mode; kind=2)\n\nShorthand for clean mode plot. See also mode_plot.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.clean_mode_plot"},{"category":"function","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.colorbar2d_plot","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"colorbar2d_plot(ratio=5)\n\n2D colorbar for HSV-RGBA images. See also phasemap.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.colorbar2d_plot"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.mode_plot-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"mode_plot(\n    mode; R=1, kind=0, legend=true,\n    boundary=true, circle=true, yflip=false, clean=false\n    )\n\nPlot intensity (kind = 0), phase (kind = 1) or combination (kind = 2) of a mode.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.mode_plot"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.phasemap-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"phasemap(mode; cmap=hsv, yflip=false, square=true)\n\nTranslate (complex) matrix into HSV-RGBA image.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.phasemap"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.ps_plot-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ps_plot(ph; R=1, r0=0, legend=true, boundary=true)\n\nPhase screen plot with optional scale bar for r0 != 0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.ps_plot"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.s_plot-Tuple{Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"s_plot(svs; m=-1)\n\nSingularvalue plot with optional indicator at index m.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.s_plot"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Plotting.tmat_plot-Tuple{Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"tmat_plot(tmat; grid=true, kind=0, legend=true, yflip=true, square=false)\n\nTransmission matrix plot of different kinds. See also mode_plot.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Plotting.tmat_plot"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PowerSpectra._oce_delta-Tuple{Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"_oce_delta(k, eta, C1)\n\nHelp function for ocespec. See also [`ocespec`](@ref).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PowerSpectra._oce_delta"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PowerSpectra.atm_spec-Tuple{Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"atm_spec(k; L0=Inf, l0=0, alpha=5/3)\n\nAtmospheric phase power spectrum. E.g. for\n\nL0=Inf, l0=0, alpha=5/3: Kolmogorov\nL0=Inf, l0=0, alpha=2  : quadratic approximation\nL0<Inf, l0=0, alpha=5/3: von Karman\nL0<Inf, l0>0, alpha=5/3: Tatarskii.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PowerSpectra.atm_spec"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PowerSpectra.atm_struct-Tuple{Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"atm_struct(r; L0=Inf)\n\nTheoretical structure function of Kolmogorov (L0=Inf) or von Karman (L0 < Inf) turbulence.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PowerSpectra.atm_struct"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PowerSpectra.oce_spec-Tuple{Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"oce_spec(k; w=-0.5, eta=0.1)\n\nOceanic phase power spectrum based on Korotkova (2018).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PowerSpectra.oce_spec"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.PowerSpectra.ps2struct-Tuple{Function, Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ps2struct(pow_spec, r; kwargs...)\n\nNumerical conversion of a given phase power spectrum to its structure function, the kwargs... are passed to pow_spec. See also atm_spec, oce_spec.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.PowerSpectra.ps2struct"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.ang_spec_prop-Tuple{Matrix, Vararg{Number, 4}}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"ang_spec_prop(u1, wvl, d1, d2, z)\n\nFresnel angular spectrum propagation based on [Schmidt (2010)].\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.ang_spec_prop"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.cn2-Tuple{Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"cn2(r0, wvl, z)\n\nRefractive index structure constant C_n^2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.cn2"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.cn2sr-Tuple{Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"cn2sr(sr2, wvl, z)\n\nRefractive index structure constant C_n^2 via Rytov variance sr2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.cn2sr"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.delta_tmat-Tuple{Matrix, Matrix, Real}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"detla_tmat(tmat1, tmat2, deltat)\n\nDifference quotient of transmission matrices. BETA!\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.delta_tmat"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.fraunhofer_prop-Tuple{Matrix, Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"fraunhofer_prop(u1, wvl, d1, z)\n\nFraunhofer propagation based on Schmidt (2010).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.fraunhofer_prop"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.gws_q-Tuple{Matrix, Matrix, Matrix, Real}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"gws_q(tmat0, tmat1, tmat2, deltat)\n\nGeneralized Wigner-Smith Q. BETA!\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.gws_q"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.lens_against_ft-Tuple{Matrix, Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"lens_against_ft(u1, wvl, d1, f)\n\nPropagation from the pupil plane to the focal plane of a lens for an object placed against (or just before) the lens.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.lens_against_ft"},{"category":"function","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.min_ns","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"min_ns(z, wvl, r0, limit=0.5)\n\nDetermine the minimal number of propagation steps while complying with the weak scintillaiton condition (default sr2 < limit = 0.5).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.min_ns"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.modeset_propagation-Tuple{Array, Number, Vector, Vector, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"modeset_propagation(modes, wvl, Rarray, zarray, phz)\n\nPropagate a whole set of modes through a channel. See also propagate.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.modeset_propagation"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.multi_step_variable-Tuple{Matrix, Number, Vector, Vector, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"multi_step_variable(uin, wvl, darray, zarray, phz; track=false)\n\nMulti step propagation along a channel described by darray, zarray and phz.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.multi_step_variable"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.principal_modes-Tuple{Matrix, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"principal_modes(gws, lgs)\n\nPrincipal modes. BETA!\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.principal_modes"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.propagate-Tuple{Matrix, Number, Vector, Vector, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"propagate(mode, wvl, Rarray, zarray, phz)\n\nPropagate through a channel (including numerical padding and cropping). See also multi_step_variable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.propagate"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.r0step-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"r0step(r0, ns)\n\nFried parameter of individual propagation steps (assumes equal step length), based on Eq.~(5.68) in [Sorelli (2019)].\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.r0step"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.rayleigh_length-Tuple{Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"rayleigh_length(w0, wvl)\n\nRayleigh length of optical propagation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.rayleigh_length"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.sigma_R2-Tuple{Number, Number, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"sigma_R2(wvl, z, r0)\n\nRytov variance.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.sigma_R2"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.sigma_R2_1-NTuple{4, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"sigma_R2_1(wvl, z, r0, ns)\n\nFist (and largest) term of Rytov variance for multi step propagation as given in Eq.~(5.72) in [Sorelli (2019)]. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.sigma_R2_1"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.svd_lgs_pixel-Tuple{Array, Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"svd_lgs_pixel(lgs, tmat)\n\nSingular modes via SVD of a transmission matrix tmat with output pixel basis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.svd_lgs_pixel"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.svd_lgs_square-Tuple{Array, Array, Matrix}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"svd_lgs_square(lgs, lgs_turb, tmat)\n\nSingular modes via SVD of a square transmission matrix tmat.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.svd_lgs_square"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.svd_square_wrapper-Tuple{Int64, Number, Number, Number, Vector, Vector, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"svd_square_wrapper(Nin, R, w0, nmax, Rarray, zarray, phz)\n\nWrapper for all steps to obtain the singular modes of a square transmission matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.svd_square_wrapper"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.transmission_pixel-Tuple{Array, Array, Number, Vector, Vector}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"transmission_pixel(lgs, phz, wvl, Rarray, zarray)\n\nTransmission matrix of a channel with output pixel basis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.transmission_pixel"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Propagation.transmission_square-Tuple{Array, Array}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"transmission_square(lgs_vac, lgs_turb)\n\nSquare transmission matrix from vacuum propagated (lgs_vac) and turbulence propagated (lgs_turb) modes, i.e. matrix with entries <lgsvac | lgsturb>.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Propagation.transmission_square"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.chunk_avg-Tuple{Vector, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"chunk_avg(a, c)\n\nSplit 1D array into chunks of size c and compute their mean.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.chunk_avg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.phase_struct_ft-Tuple{Matrix, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"phase_struct_ft(a, R)\n\nRadial structure function of a 2D array based on Fourier Transform. Needs zeropadding. Not recommended to use, rather use phase_struct_rd.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.phase_struct_ft"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.phase_struct_rd-Tuple{Matrix, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"phase_struct_rd(ph, R; rs=0, samples=10^8)\n\nRadial phase structure function of a 2D array based on random sampling.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.phase_struct_rd"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.points_in_circ-Tuple{Number, Integer}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"points_in_circ(radius, samples)\n\nUnifromly distributed random points confined by a circle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.points_in_circ"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.radial_avg-Tuple{Matrix, Number}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"radial_avg(a, d)\n\nAverage of a 2D array along centered circles.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.radial_avg"},{"category":"method","location":"#SingularModes.Statistics.zernike_covariance-Tuple{Function}","page":"SingularModes.jl","text":"zernike_covariance(\n    pow_spec;\n    nmaxScreen=9,\n    nmaxZernike=10,\n    samples=10,\n    rs=0,\n    N=1024,\n    R=1,\n    zks=zeros(1,1,1),\n    kwargs...\n    )\n\nZernike variance of screens for a given power spectrum. See also SingularModes.PhaseScreens.zk_overlap, SingularModes.PhaseScreens.ph_x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SingularModes.Statistics.zernike_covariance"}]
}
